article.headline: Cornell 85, Brown 45
article.story: PROVIDENCE, R.I. -- Jeff Foote had 16 points and nine rebounds, while Ryan Wittman added 15 points as Cornell routed Brown, 85-45, on Saturday night. Cornell's victory combined with Columbia's loss to Yale enabled the Big Red (18-8, 8-2 Ivy League) to increase their lead over the second-place Lions to two games. Peter Sullivan led the Bears (7-17, 1-9 Ivy League), who've lost six straight to Cornell, with 12 points. Cornell switched between zone and man-to-man defenses while holding Brown to a season-low 45 points. The score was tied three times in the first 3:48, the last at 6-6, before Cornell went on a 9-0 run. Cornell also scored the first 10 points of the second half to increase its lead to 54-27. The Big Red, who're 13-2 in their last 15 games, scored 40 points in the paint and 20 points off 18 Brown turnovers.
